{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775863628732,"sessionID":"ses_28647907bffeG1elcpk3YIiBxb","part":{"id":"prt_d79b883b7001Tm0aboJUzmtZa8","messageID":"msg_d79b87e16001eWQ7fYG2qXEhOR","sessionID":"ses_28647907bffeG1elcpk3YIiBxb","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863662903,"sessionID":"ses_28647907bffeG1elcpk3YIiBxb","part":{"id":"prt_d79b88c8f001JFogxKkN8PEA1p","messageID":"msg_d79b87e16001eWQ7fYG2qXEhOR","sessionID":"ses_28647907bffeG1elcpk3YIiBxb","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_49e566bcfbc64c81a5cebfb6","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Proposal: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement `CodeInterpreterClient` — the primary public-facing Python client for the AgentCube SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). This client enables users to programmatically create and manage Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execute code, run commands, and manage files through the Router (data plane).\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **`CodeInterpreterClient`** (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n   - Context manager lifecycle (`__enter__` / `__exit__`)\n   - Session creation via `ControlPlaneClient` or reuse of existing `session_id`\n   - Data plane initialization with `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n   - Public methods: `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, `stop`\n\n2. **`ControlPlaneClient`** (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n   - HTTP session management with connection pooling\n   - `create_session` — POST to `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter`\n   - `delete_session` — DELETE with 404-tolerant behavior\n   - Auth token resolution from argument or Kubernetes SA token file\n\n3. **`CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`** (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n   - Router-relative base URL construction via `urljoin`\n   - `execute_command` with PicoD timeout buffer logic (`timeout + 2.0s`)\n   - `run_code` with timestamped `.py` file write-and-execute path for Python\n   - File operations: `write_file` (base64 JSON), `upload_file` (multipart), `download_file` (streamed GET), `list_files`\n   - Session header management: `x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n4. **Supporting utilities**\n   - `create_session` — `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` pooling\n   - `read_token_from_file` — SA token file reader\n   - `get_logger` — structured logger factory\n\n5. **Exception hierarchy** (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n   - `AgentCubeError` (base), `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- `AgentRuntimeClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` (separate AR)\n- CLI tooling, examples, e2e test scripts\n- Packaging/publishing infrastructure (pyproject.toml exists)\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Current | After | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `requests` | — | Required | HTTP client for control and data plane |\n| `PyJWT>=2.0.0` | — | Required | Token handling |\n| `cryptography` | — | Required | Token/crypto utilities |\n| Python | — | >=3.10 | Minimum version |\n\n### Affected Components\n\n- **Downstream consumers**: Any Python application importing `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient`\n- **Upstream services**: Workload Manager (control plane), Router (data plane), PicoD code execution engine\n- **No breaking changes**: This is a new module; no existing public APIs are modified\n\n### Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|\n| Data plane init failure leaks control plane session | Medium | Cleanup logic in `_init_data_plane` catches, deletes session, re-raises |\n| Router URL not configured | Low | Explicit `ValueError` at construction time |\n| Timeout mismatch causing premature ReadTimeout | Medium | PicoD buffer logic (`timeout + 2.0s`) on execute_command read side |\n| SA token file unreadable in non-K8s environments | Low | `read_token_from_file` returns `\"\"` on `FileNotFoundError`; auth header omitted gracefully |\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### 1. Single unified client vs. layered clients\n\n**Considered**: One `AgentCubeClient` class handling both control plane and data plane operations internally.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Separation of concerns: control plane (session lifecycle) and data plane (execution) have different HTTP contracts, timeouts, and auth requirements\n- Testability: isolated clients are easier to mock and unit test\n- Extensibility: `AgentRuntimeClient` follows the same layered pattern; consistency matters\n\n### 2. Configuration dataclass vs. distributed defaults\n\n**Considered**: A single `Configuration` dataclass (like many SDKs) to hold all settings.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- The existing codebase resolves config at the component level (constructor args → env vars → file fallback)\n- A unified config class would add indirection without reducing complexity given the divergent settings between control plane and data plane clients\n- Distributed resolution is simpler for the current surface area\n\n### 3. Async HTTP client (aiohttp/httpx) vs. synchronous requests\n\n**Considered**: Using an async HTTP client for non-blocking I/O.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Target users are scripting/automation workflows where synchronous blocking is acceptable\n- `requests` is already the established dependency in the codebase\n- Async would significantly increase complexity (event loop management, async context managers) without clear benefit for the M-sized scope\n- Can be revisited in a future async-specific AR if demand arises\n\n### 4. gRPC vs. REST for data plane\n\n**Considered**: Using gRPC for data plane communication.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- The Router already exposes REST endpoints; the SDK is a client, not a server\n- gRPC would require proto definitions and code generation, increasing build complexity\n- REST is sufficient for the current request/response patterns (execute, file upload/download)\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n1. **Exceptions** — Define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`\n2. **Utilities** — Implement `create_session`, `read_token_from_file`, `get_logger`\n3. **ControlPlaneClient** — HTTP session, create/delete session methods\n4. **CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient** — Base URL construction, execute, file operations, timeout buffer logic\n5. **CodeInterpreterClient** — Public API, context manager, session lifecycle, data plane delegation\n6. **Public exports** — Wire `__init__.py` and `clients/__init__.py`\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- `CodeInterpreterClient` can be used as a context manager to execute Python code and shell commands\n- Session lifecycle is correctly managed (create → use → cleanup on exit)\n- Data plane init failure does not leak control plane sessions\n- `CommandExecutionError` is raised for non-zero exit codes with full context\n- All public methods delegate correctly to underlying data plane client\n- Package imports cleanly: `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient`\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775863662896,"end":1775863662901}}}}
